│ This bug is caused by an assertion failure in the loop       │
│ vectorizer's VPlan execution phase. The `VPInstruction` for  │
│ `PtrAdd` (which models a `getelementptr` with a single       │
│ index) incorrectly assumes its pointer operand can always be │
│ fetched as a scalar value.                                   │
│                                                              │
│ In the provided reproducer, the pointer operand is an        │
│ induction variable that is uniform across all vector lanes.  │
│ The VPlan represents this uniform value using a              │
│ `VPReplicateRecipe`. During code generation, this recipe     │
│ produces a vector value (by broadcasting the scalar).        │
│ However, the `PtrAdd` recipe tries to fetch this value as a  │
│ scalar using `VPTransformState::get(..., IsScalar=true)`.    │
│ This mismatch triggers an assertion in                       │
│ `VPTransformState::get`, as it's being asked for a scalar    │
│ value for a `VPValue` that has been materialized as a        │
│ vector.                                                      │
│                                                              │
│ The fix is to modify the `PtrAdd` recipe's code generation   │
│ logic. Before fetching the pointer operand, it should check  │
│ if the operand is defined by a `VPReplicateRecipe`.          │
│ - If it is, it should fetch the value as a vector, and then  │
│ extract the first element to get the scalar pointer.         │
│ - If it is not, it can proceed with fetching the value as a  │
│ scalar, as it did before.                                    │
│                                                              │
│ This change correctly handles both cases: uniform pointer    │
│ operands represented by `VPReplicateRecipe` and other scalar │
│ pointer operands. A check for `getDefiningRecipe()`          │
│ returning null is also added to handle live-in values and    │
│ constants that don't have a defining recipe.                 │
│                                                              │
│ ```patch                                                     │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp         │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp         │
│ @@ -645,8 +645,17 @@                                         │
│    case VPInstruction::PtrAdd: {                             │
│      assert(vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) &&              │
│             "can only generate first lane for PtrAdd");      │
│ -    Value *Ptr = State.get(getOperand(0), /* IsScalar */    │
│ true);                                                       │
│ +    Value *Ptr;                                             │
│ +    VPValue *PtrOp = getOperand(0);                         │
│ +    VPRecipeBase *Def = PtrOp->getDefiningRecipe();         │
│ +    if (Def && isa<VPReplicateRecipe>(Def)) {               │
│ +      Value *VectorPtr = State.get(PtrOp);                  │
│ +      Ptr = Builder.CreateExtractElement(VectorPtr,         │
│ Builder.getInt32(0));                                        │
│ +    } else {                                                │
│ +      Ptr = State.get(PtrOp, /* IsScalar */ true);          │
│ +    }                                                       │
│      Value *Addend = State.get(getOperand(1), /* IsScalar */ │
│ true);                                                       │
│      return isInBounds() ? Builder.CreateInBoundsPtrAdd(Ptr, │
│ Addend, Name)                                                │
│                           : Builder.CreatePtrAdd(Ptr,        │
│ Addend, Name);                                               │
│    }                                                         │
│                                                              │
│ ```                                                          │
